headline: Leiter IT Infrastruktur und Sicherheit bei E+E Elektronik
organization_description_1: E+E Elektronik develops and manufactures sensors and transmitters for humidity, dew point, moisture in oil, CO2, air velocity, mass flow, temperature and pressure. Hand-held meters, humidity calibration systems and calibration services complete the comprehensive product portfolio of the Austrian sensor specialist.    The main areas of application are HVAC and building technology, industrial measurement technology, the automotive industry, pharmaceutical and food industry, cleanroom technology, meteorology, environmental technology and agricultural engineering.  E+E Elektronik has subsidiaries in China, Germany, France, Italy, Korea, USA and India and is represented by over 60 sales partners worldwide.  As a company with a firm commitment to quality, E+E Elektronik has an established and certified quality management system in accordance with ISO 9001 and IATF 16949. E+E also places great value on environmental protection and is therefore certified in accordance with environmental standard ISO 14001 and has been a partner of the Climate Alliance Austria for many years.   E+E Elektronik is accredited as a calibration laboratory according to EN ISO/IEC 17025 with the identification number 0608 by Akkreditierung Austria / Federal Ministry for Digital and Economic Affairs. The services of the accredited laboratory include manufacturer-independent calibrations of measuring instruments for the measurands humidity, dew point, CO‚ÇÇ, air velocity, air flow, temperature and pressure.  Furthermore, E+E Elektronik has been appointed by the Federal Office of Metrology and Surveying (BEV) to maintain as designated institute the national standards for humidity, dew point, air velocity and gas concentration CO‚ÇÇ in Austria.

organization_description_1: Welcome to Bruker Alicona!
